      "content": "Originalists would vehemently reject the notion that their methodology is merely a political tool; they see it as a commitment to objective legal principles. They argue that the text and original meaning are the only legitimate sources of law, and any judge who ignores that is simply making up law. To claim it's just a political mask ignores the rigorous intellectual effort required to ascertain historical meaning, which is a neutral, scholarly pursuit.",
